dataIdInfo.idAbs: This dataset contains the extent and names of selected River Basins in the State of Queensland
dataIdInfo.idPurp: To provide an authorative single point of truth for the extent of selected River Basins in the State Queensland. It is suitable for use in land administration, emergency and water management, monitoring of climate change, hydrological modelling, topographic and vegetation mapping and in the production of navigational and web based mapping applications.

dataIdInfo.suppInfo:
The dataset was captured at 1:100 000.
The seaward edge of this data aligns with the Coastline and State Border - Queensland dataset.
Feature Types: RIVER BASIN – The extent of the catchment of a major river calculated from a gauging station at the confluence of the river
Attributes: RIVER_NAME - The name of the river, the basin is associated with. BASIN_NUMBER - A unique ID number allocated to the Drainage Basin the river is in e.g. the Bremer River is in the Brisbane Drainage Basin. The Basin_Number is 143, the unique ID number for the Brisbane Drainage Basin
This dataset is stored in an ESRI Geodatabase. Some columns names may be shortened if downloaded in the ESRI shape format.

dataLineage.statement:
The location of the gauging station at the confluence of the river was sourced from the Gauging Station Catchments - Queensland dataset. The extent of the basin was then compiled by comparing 1:100000 topographic mapping (published and unpublished) and determining the watershed based on the contours and plotting this line onto hard copy maps. These plotted lines were later digitised to create a spatial dataset. With the 1:250000 drainage network as a background, checks were made to ensure that no drainage lines crossed a basin boundary.
River Basins are subsets of and have boundaries that are aligned to and nested with the associated Drainage Basin. Please refer to the Drainage Basin - Queensland dataset.
In 2020, the seaward edge of the data was moved to align with the Coastline and State Border - Queensland dataset.
